parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to become immobile, leading to a potential safety risk, especially if it occurs at high speeds. This can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the transfer case
making it impossible to drive the vehicle
transmission fluid leaking from the transfer case
clutch not releasing into gear due to hydraulic cylinder malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft bearings can cause the crankshaft to move excessively, leading to engine damage, stalling, and potentially rendering the vehicle immobile. This can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The crankshaft has excessive front-end play
the crankshaft can be physically moved by hand left and right and up and down

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EGR valve can cause the check engine light to come on, potentially leading to engine damage and decreased performance.
The failure of the turbo engine belt can cause engine damage, stalling, and potentially rendering the vehicle immobile. This can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the head gasket and valves can cause engine damage, stalling, and potentially rendering the vehicle immobile. This can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the turbo hose can cause oil pressure to lower, fluid to leak onto the engine block, and potentially lead to engine damage.
symptoms: fluid leaks onto the engine block.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower ball joints can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and can also result in premature wear on other suspension components.
symptoms: Loud banging noise from the rear
rubbing or humming noise from the front

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Repair of Ball Joints under Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly repair or replace ball joints under recall can lead to continued safety risks and premature wear on other suspension components.
symptoms: but potential symptoms include loud banging noise from the rear
rubbing or humming noise from the front

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Leaking struts can cause uneven vehicle ride, reduced handling, and increased stopping distances, which can lead to accidents.
